cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with image-based camera localization and visual SLAM systems, which are primarily computer vision and robotics topics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning and neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of GPS and visual odometry for camera localization indicates that it could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves loss functions and optimization, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for text summarization, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
